notesStmt.note: Condition: Copy has occasional ink smudges; f. 3r rather smeared; small hole in lower portion of a few leaves with minor damage to text (f. 50-51).
Copy has ms. shelf-mark in pencil and ms. inscription ("Marc. II., 12") on f. 1r; ms. inscription ("Marc. XIV 14") on f. 95v; some marginal annotations.

msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Part of the New Testament containing the Gospel of Mark 2.12-16.14 inclusive.

respStmt.name: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 96; 1-39, [i], 40-95; modern Roman script foliation in pencil, upper left recto. Catchwords on versos, lower center.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in primarily black ink (1 line in red on f. 86r) in 10-11 lines per page on coarse paper; text area frame-ruled in blind.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a clumsy and inexperienced naskh in black ink with poor spelling and omissions caused by homoioteleuta.

origin.p: No indication of date, place, or copyist but probably mid-18th to mid-19th century.

history.provenance: Presented to the Library of the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning by Dr. Cyrus Adler.
